---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Kipa - how we collect, use, and protect your data."
  canonical="/privacy"
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-content">
      <header>
        <a href="/" class="back-link">Kipa</a>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect information you provide directly when you create an account, including your email address and display name. We also collect the links, notes, and categories you save within the App. When you enable notifications, we register your device with our notification provider so we can deliver push messages you opt into.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>
          We use your information to provide, maintain, and improve the App. This includes storing your saved links and notes, syncing your data across devices, processing subscriptions, measuring product usage and stability, and—where permitted—understanding how marketing campaigns lead people to install the App. We do not sell your personal information to third parties.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is stored securely using Firebase and related Google Cloud services. We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information, including encryption in transit and at rest. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We use the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Firebase Authentication, Cloud Firestore, and Cloud Storage (Google) for accounts and your content</li>
          <li>Firebase Analytics (Google) for product analytics</li>
          <li>Firebase Crashlytics (Google) for crash and error diagnostics</li>
          <li>Tenjin for install and campaign attribution on mobile</li>
          <li>RevenueCat for subscription management and purchase validation</li>
          <li>Apple Sign In and Google Sign-In for authentication</li>
          <li>Expo push notification services for device token registration and delivery</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These services have their own privacy policies governing their use of your data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Analytics, Diagnostics, and Attribution</h2>
        <p>
          We use Firebase Analytics to understand feature usage and flows within the App. For signed-in users, we may associate analytics events with a stable app user identifier and, in some cases, set analytics properties such as your email address to connect usage with your account in our analytics tools.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use Firebase Crashlytics to collect diagnostic information when the App crashes or encounters certain errors, to help us fix issues.
        </p>
        <p>
          On Apple devices, we use Apple's App Tracking Transparency framework. If you allow tracking, our attribution partner (Tenjin) may use the identifier for advertisers (IDFA) and related signals to measure whether ads or campaigns led to an install. If you do not allow tracking, we do not use the IDFA for that purpose through that flow.
        </p>
        <p>
          We configure Google Analytics consent settings on iOS so that advertising-related measurement aligns with your tracking choice while allowing us to continue product analytics where appropriate.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Push Notifications</h2>
        <p>
          If you grant notification permission, we may send push notifications related to the App, such as reminders or updates about your saved links or account. You can turn off notifications at any time in your device settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information at any time. You can delete your account and all associated data from the Account screen in the App (tap "Delete Account" at the bottom) or by contacting us directly at <a href="mailto:privacy@kipaapp.com">privacy@kipaapp.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your data for as long as your account is active. If you delete your account, we will delete your personal data within 30 days, except where we are required to retain it for legal purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The App is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will delete it immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy in the App and updating the "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@kipaapp.com">privacy@kipaapp.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
  }

  .legal-content header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: #9c7ed4;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-content h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #5a5568;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.5rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: #9c7ed4;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
